Heat broiler to high. Bring a #large pot{} of salted water to a boil. Wash and dry produce.

Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Peel and mince @garlic{1%clove}.

Once water is boiling, add @rigatoni pasta{6%ounce} to #pot{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until
al dente, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Reserve ½ cup pasta cooking water, then drain.

While pasta cooks, heat a large drizzle of @?cooking oil{2%teaspoon} in a large, preferably
ovenproof, pan over medium-high heat. Add half the @ground plant-based protein{9%ounce}.
Using a #spatula{}, press into an even layer; cook, undisturbed, until browned on the bottom,
~{3-4%minutes}. (Save any remaining plant-based protein for another use.)

Break up protein into pieces and continue cooking until browned all over and warmed through,
~{3-4%minutes} more. Add scallion whites, garlic, @Tuscan Heat Spice{1%tablespoon}, @salt{}, and
@pepper{}; cook, stirring, until scallions are slightly softened, ~{1%minute}.

Add @crushed tomatoes{13.76%ounce} and @sugar{1%teaspoon} to pan with plant-based protein.

Pour in ½ cup plain water, @salt{}, and @pepper{}; bring to a boil. Reduce heat to medium low
and simmer until slightly thickened, ~{5-7%minutes}.

Stir in @cream cheese{2%tablespoon} and @butter{1%tablespoon} until melted and combined.

While sauce simmers, in a #small bowl{}, combine @panko breadcrumbs{¼%cup} with
@olive oil{1%tablespoon}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Stir drained rigatoni into pan with sauce. If needed, stir in reserved pasta cooking water a
splash at a time until rigatoni is thoroughly coated in sauce. Taste and season with @salt{}
and @pepper{}.

> If your pan isn't ovenproof, transfer mixture now to a #baking dish{}.

Evenly sprinkle with @Italian cheese blend{½%cup} and panko mixture.

Broil pasta until cheese melts and panko is browned, ~{2-4%minutes}.

> Watch carefully to avoid burning.

Sprinkle with scallion greens. Divide between plates and serve.